de.unlixx.runpng.bitmap

Class Bitmap32Sequence

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.unlixx.runpng.bitmap.Bitmap32Sequence

  • public class Bitmap32Sequence
extends java.lang.Object
    Bitmap32Sequence for animation usage. This class is used to transport single and multiple Bitmap32 objects from and to storage. It holds also common png chunks like PLTE, trNS, acTL, tEXt etc.

      • Bitmap32Sequence

        public Bitmap32Sequence(Bitmap32 bitmap,
                        boolean bOptimized,
                        PngAnimationType animType)
        Constructor with a default bitmap and an animation type. The png header will be built automatically.
        Parameters:
        bitmap - A Bitmap32 object.
        bOptimized - True if this sequence should be seen and handled as already optimized.
        animType - A PngAnimationType enum type.

      • Bitmap32Sequence

        public Bitmap32Sequence(PngHeader header,
                        boolean bOptimized)
        Constructor with a given header. This will normally be used by the Bitmap32Manager in a read process while receiving the header chunk. The default bitmap will be built as a transparent rectangle by information from the header.
        Parameters:
        header - A PngHeader object.
        bOptimized - True if this sequence should be seen and handled as already optimized.
